# Address Indexing Flow Rule

This rule governs address indexing behavior only.

## 1) Canonical flow
1. Trigger indexing for address list (`indexAddressesList`).
2. Poll workflow status per address (`getAddressIndexingJobStatus`).
3. Fetch token pages incrementally while job is active.
4. Ingest fetched tokens into local DB immediately.
5. Stop when terminal status is reached.

## 2) Incremental UX requirement
- On each status poll while non-terminal, fetch and ingest available token pages.
- Users must see partial token results before job completion.

## 3) Terminal state handling
- Stop polling when `status.isDone == true`.
- `completed`: success path.
- `failed` or `canceled`: terminal error path; stop fetching.

## 4) Data integrity constraints
- Preserve per-address workflow mapping (`address <-> workflow_id`).
- Avoid duplicate token ingestion for the same address/page cursor.
- Keep poll loop idempotent and resumable.
